{
  "texts": [
    "This generative pre-training method trains models to reconstruct images from partially obscured inputs, aiding in understanding the underlying structure of visual data.",
    "• Contrastive Language-image Pre-training: An innovative method, contrastive language-image pre-training [50] (CLIP), involves training a vision model using diverse image-text datasets.",
    "The model learns to match images with corresponding texts within a mini-batch through contrastive learning.",
    "CLIP shows impressive zero-shot capabilities, performing on par with traditional models like ResNet [35] on ImageNet without task-specific training.",
    "Text descriptions enhance understanding of the visual content, facilitating the model's comprehension of visual elements and their interrelations, which is essential for effective learning."
  ]
}